  "Description_v1" : "Credit Agricole NYC expansion and FIX",
  "LongDescription_v2" : "Credit Agricole Fixed Income in London, the EGB (European Government Bonds) trading desk, have successfully introduced a pricing algorithm built with StreamBase. This algorithm does not trade automatically; rather, it makes better prices available to human traders. The algo has produced measurable business improvements e.g. attaining a 40% wallet share (the bank's share of a client's total business in the market) for a key valued client. The success of this algo means the bank proposes to duplicate its use in New York, for US Treasury instruments. Since the bank doesn't currently have the means to trade US Treasuries, they have selected a broker, which offers a FIX interface. So there are two parts to this initiative: expansion of the StreamBase footprint into NYC, and, optional but seems quite likely, use of the StreamBase FIX adapter. We have proposed this plus PSG customisation of the \"FIX dictionaries\" for the broker's special message types.",

  },
  "OpportunityRegion_1_v6" : "France",
  "OpportunityDescription_v4" : "Auchan international division is looking for a SaaS solution to implement referencing processes to feed their Product Master Data and their Supplier Master Data systems. 
High Level Requirements:
- The solution should be available in 14 countries (Poland, Russia, Vietnam and others).
- Multi-lingual interface for the end user
- Ability to integrate with other systems via REST and SOAP
- Ability to use the case manager from a tablet
- Reporting and Analytics
- integration with electronic signatures systems



 ",
  "OpportunityOpentopics_v9" : "Potential blockers:
- It is yet to be confirmed whether running on Amazon is a show-stopper or not. Auchan does not want to give money to their competitor.
- do we crypt the data, so that Amazon cannot steal and use their data ?
- the multi-lingual thing is also to be confirmed. They would like to see the data model (eg. Supplier id label) translated in forms. they are not talking about the value, but the form element labels.
- they need the ability to select a value from a list retrieved in an external system.
- our reference customers on Live Apps.

Other important:
- Need reporting per country, per app, per custom data
- Mobile client will be needed a little later
- electronic signature for signing forms
- UI customization

 Other:
- they have seen a vendor include a sort of screencaming as a browser plugin so that a user could share issues or raise questions on a particular use case.
"
}
